***
***	<comment from="devstral-small-2">
***	The original Maude code defines a module COLLATZ that implements the Collatz conjecture using conditional rewrite rules. The code is already quite efficient and concise, but there are a few minor improvements that can be made to enhance readability and maintain the same semantics.
***	</comment>
***

mod COLLATZ is
	protecting NAT .

	*** Collatz conjecture
	*** (no one has proven that this sequence is always terminating)

	var N : Nat .

	crl [even] N => N quo 2 [owise] if N rem 2 = 0 .
	crl [odd] N => 3 * N + 1 [owise] if N rem 2 = 1 .
endm